gomodel:SYNGO_837  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The plasma membrane dopamine transporter (DAT) transports dopamine into neurons. Striatal synaptosomes from DAT-KO mice show no uptake of radiolabelled dopamine (Fig. 1d). Fast-scan cyclic voltammetry (carbon-fibre amperometry) after electrical stimulation in striatal DAT-KO slices reveals a 100times longer time for dopamine clearance in comparison to wildtype slices (Fig. 5). These findings indicate a defect in dopamine re-uptake in DAT-KO mice.. Experimental description: We have produced, by means of in vivo homologous recombination, a strain of mice in which the gene encoding the DAT has been disrupted." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_837" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

